Description. Living colonies are dish-shaped with lobed edges; some lobes are united into ridges which are placed radially on the outer part of disk. Some finger-like or lumpy lobes (up to 12 mm in height) can occur on the central part of disk (
Fig. 8
). The polyps cover the disk and lobes; they are also distributed on the lower surface of the disk but only near the edge, as a border 4–6 mm in width. The preserved holotype is funnel-shaped (
Fig. 9
), 99.6 mm high. The lower surface of the disk and stalk surface are slightly grooved longitudinally.

